<BorderPane xmlns="http://javafx.com/javafx/22" xmlns:fx="http://javafx.com/fxml/1" fx:controller="edu.augustana.Instructions">
   <center>
      <AnchorPane prefHeight="400.0" prefWidth="600.0">
         <children>
            <TabPane prefHeight="400.0" prefWidth="600.0" tabClosingPolicy="UNAVAILABLE">
              <tabs>
                <Tab text="Radio">
                  <content>
                    <AnchorPane minHeight="0.0" minWidth="0.0" prefHeight="180.0" prefWidth="200.0">
                           <children>
                              <VBox alignment="TOP_CENTER" prefHeight="372.0" prefWidth="600.0" style="-fx-background-color: #606160;">
                                 <children>
                                    <Label prefHeight="88.0" prefWidth="574.0" text="Before you do anything, you must turn on the radio. This can be done by button in bottom right hand corner of the radio. The button to the left of that is the mute button, which will silence all incoming and outgoing sound. After that, in order to hear anything, you will need to turn the volume up and open the filter. The filter is a low-pass filter, which filters out noise from outside interference, like the weather. If the filter is closed all the way, you won't be able to hear anything. " textFill="WHITE" wrapText="true">
                                       <font>
                                          <Font name="Sitka Heading" size="12.0" />
                                       </font>
                                    </Label>
                                    <Label prefHeight="48.0" prefWidth="570.0" text="You will notice the other knob controls on the radio, the band and tone controls! The band knob controls what meter band you are using, and the default is 10m. The tone knob controls your side tone, or what frequency you output CW at." textFill="WHITE" wrapText="true">
                                       <font>
                                          <Font name="Sitka Heading" size="12.0" />
                                       </font>
                                    </Label>
                                    <Label prefHeight="85.0" prefWidth="567.0" text="Now, how do you actually output some CW? We have two options for you, paddles and a straight key. For the paddles the &quot;J&quot; key will output your dots for as long as you hold the key down. The &quot;K&quot; key will do the same but for your dashes. The &quot;L&quot; key is your straight key, and it will determine dots and dashes based on how long you hold down the button. The straight key needs to be calibrated, so please type in a letter or two so that it knows how quickly or slowly you type." textFill="WHITE" wrapText="true">
                                       <font>
                                          <Font name="Sitka Heading" size="12.0" />
                                       </font>
                                    </Label>
                                    <Label prefHeight="62.0" prefWidth="562.0" text="The top slider on the bottom of the radio is a frequency filter. This will filter out incoming CW transmissions if they are far away enough from where you are tuned into. The bottom slider is your &quot;dial&quot;, which allows you to change the frequency that you are tuned into." textFill="WHITE" wrapText="true">
                                       <font>
                                          <Font name="Sitka Heading" size="12.0" />
                                       </font>
                                    </Label>
                                 </children>
                              </VBox>
                           </children>
                        </AnchorPane>
                  </content>
                </Tab>
                <Tab text="Untitled Tab 2">
                  <content>
                    <AnchorPane minHeight="0.0" minWidth="0.0" prefHeight="180.0" prefWidth="200.0" style="-fx-background-color: #606160;" />
                  </content>
                </Tab>
              </tabs>
            </TabPane>
         </children>
      </AnchorPane>
   </center>
   <bottom>
      <AnchorPane prefHeight="38.0" prefWidth="600.0" BorderPane.alignment="TOP_CENTER">
         <children>
            <Button alignment="CENTER" layoutX="274.0" layoutY="6.0" mnemonicParsing="false" text="Ok!" />
         </children>
      </AnchorPane>
   </bottom>
</BorderPane>
